<font color="#FF0000">WHAT I HAD - WHAT I HAVE LEFT!</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov  3  2:17:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Silent Warrior mentions character.  Where do we get it?<br>
If you know how to swim.. because someone gave you those skills..you can swim in a cess pool or a clear lake. It is a moot point where you have swam.  The question is can you swim or not?<br>
Men went to Vietnam without character and acquired some character or returned without character.<br>
Some went with character.. acquired more or lost what they had.<br>
I really don't want to believe that war builds character but it does... trial and tribulation seems to create stronger backs along with stronger spirituality etc.  My sense of brotherhood with some veterans is a product of the war.  But I do not give blanket acceptance to every veteran...I saw some of the sorriest people I have ever know in Vietnam..enlisted and officer.  I was my best and worst in Vietnam.  Possibly, the war was a winnowing process where the chafe was separated from the wheat.  If you didn't go there with a good wheat/chafe ratio..you didn't gain much.<br>
I still believe that war impacts upon emotions and the ability to control the same.  Emotional diarreah has a tendency to wipe out your smarts.<br>
Any war would have caused us the same horror or trauma.  But a different style of nurturing after the exposure would have made all the difference in the world!  You don't have to be a brain surgeon to realize that how you handle trauma from the get go has a lot of impact on the rapidity and quality of the recovery.  Sloppy handling of a neck injury can cause a permanent problem.  Sloppy treatment, no treatment or aggrivation of emotional wounds in war veterans can put some serious maladies into concrete.<br>
The individual's character and inner strengths are critical for a person asked - forced to fight.  But a greater consequence is contingent upon the character of the nation of people he serves.  We were not supported.. that can not be undone.  We were wounded going and coming..that can not be undone. Some of us will survive with our scars or with open wounds.. only because of brother's who care..family and friends who care and people of character who haven't been traumatized..who care!<br>
Almost everything that happens to us we cause it or let it!<br>
If it weren't for other people on the earth..then we could remove the &quot;almost!&quot;<br>
You don't need others &quot;to help you.&quot;  You need others to &quot;help you help yourself!&quot;  There is a difference.<br>
Without my Brothers of Choice it would be a very hard row to hoe..but I would make it.. or die trying.<br>
You can take a man's life but you can't take his character. Because if you do..he didn't have it to start with.<br>
There are some on this site who had it..still have it and always will have it.  It's just a little dented and torn.<br><br>
Thanks Silent Warrior!<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
